{
  "texts": [
    "Deep neural networks trainingThis section describes the methodology for training the model, which involved using a realistic GNSS signal simulator to generate I &Q samples from GPS L1 C/A satellites.",
    "The simulator was used to vary parameters according to the training plan outlined in this section.",
    "To improve the detection and localization accuracy, a higher sampling frequency may be desirable, since it increases the correlation between samples around the CAF peak.",
    "However, this also impacts the number of samples to be processed, and a trade-off must be considered.",
    "Therefore, the sampling frequency was increased to 4 MHz from the previously used 2 MHz in our initial work [29]."
  ]
}